---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import EmailSignup from '../components/EmailSignup.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Coral Reaper"
  description="Coral Reaper is a small, US-based aquaculture operation focused on hand-selected frags, honest photography, and overnight shipping."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Small operation. Tight catalog. No filler.</h1>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Coral Reaper is a small, US-based aquaculture project. We grow, frag,
          and ship corals we'd be proud to keep in our own systems — nothing
          more, nothing less.
        </p>

        <h2>What we believe</h2>
        <p>
          Aquacultured corals are stronger, hardier, and easier to settle into
          a new system than wild collected pieces. They've already adapted to
          captive water, captive lighting, and captive flow. We focus on
          tank-raised stock for that reason — it's better for hobbyists and
          better for reefs.
        </p>

        <h2>How we ship</h2>
        <p>
          What you see is what ships. Every frag is photographed under
          actinic-only lighting on a black background — no edited stock photos,
          no bait-and-switch substitutions. Frags ship overnight with a heat
          or cold pack as the route requires, and a live arrival guarantee.
          Cut corners on packaging is how corals die in transit; we don't.
        </p>

        <h2>Why "Reaper"</h2>
        <p>
          The name's a wink. The corals you'll find here are the survivors —
          tank-raised, dialed-in, and ready to spread. The reaper is the one
          who picks the keepers.
        </p>

        <h2>Where we are in the launch</h2>
        <p>
          The list is open now. Storefront and first drop are coming soon.
          Wholesale and partnership inquiries are welcome — see the
          <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="signup-spacer">
        <EmailSignup />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .narrow {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .prose {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .prose h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    color: var(--color-bone);
  }

  .prose p {
    color: var(--color-bone-dim);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    max-width: 65ch;
  }

  .signup-spacer {
    margin-top: var(--space-16);
  }
</style>
